  "text": "Here we present a new approach to overcome these limitations -we exploit the modal properties of light propagation in tapered optical fibers (TFs) to structure light collection patterns on their large optically active area and to access deeper cells. In addition to be less invasive than FFs [CITATION_1] , TFs probes have unique light collection features: (i) a more uniform interface over up to 2 mm of tissue along the fiber axis, (ii) the ability to perform multisite collection along the taper by time-division multiplexing, and (iii) the ability to design arbitrary collection volumes by micro-structuring the non-planar surface of the fiber taper.",
